I had dinner at Vrindavan Restaurant with my Mother/ Sister and sister daughter. We ordered Plain Rava Dosa and clearly requested for it to be soft as my mother had bad teeth. But the waiter brought a crispy one and we asked him to get a soft one which he brought fifteen minutes later surprisingly the brought in Rava Dosa was again not soft but my mother insisted not to again request for a change and had it forcibly. The dish I ordered was Paneer Kathi Roll which was too sticky and gummy. The chapati roll stuck in my mouth like fevicol and the stuffing was yuck. My sister ordered an Onion Uttapam which was brought in crusty and dark in color and it looked to be burnt and tasted like hell. Only the pasta that my sister daughter ordered was ok and she finished with some satisfaction. For dessert I asked the floor manager who had a crew cut whether the gajar halwa was prepared with Delhi Carrot or Chennai Carrot and his reply was that he had no idea about it as it was brought from outside ( Surprising) as if their kitchen does not prepare Gajar ka Halwa. I had to go for Gulab Jamun and My sister ordered Ice cream Sundae .The environment was dull with lighting too dim and waiters confused about orders wherein one waiter brought us rice and another brought us Ghee Masala Dosa , Both of which we had not ordered and we had to ask him to take it back. Atrocious Place to have Dinner.
By the Way the Krishna Restaurant across this place where I and my Mother usually go Serves excellent Food with exemplary service , Unfortunately we shortlisted Vrindavan instead of Krishna for our outing which was a DISASTER.

The staff sometimes just forget the orders and we have to remind them, which is a letdown since they seem to provide great hospitality at the start.

I would suggest this place anyday, the prices are affordable, great location, enough parking spaces, and amazing book collection.

text.text:
This review is for Pet parents out there looking for a place to dine with your dog. The place is very comfortable and not too crowded for your fur babies. They’re also quite accommodative. I ordered a bowl of chicken for Joey (my retriever) and it’s a decent quantity that you get.

Human food quantity is pretty good and filling. We were 2 of us and we had a low appetite, so if you’re someone who comes with little appetite, the food can easily serve 3.

However, if it’s your first time with your dog:
1. Make sure they finish their business before you taken them as the place is filled with greenery- enough to trigger them
2. There are 2 cats, quite friendly and didn’t bother though, so if your pet reacts to them, make sure to carry the treats or order something for them too
3. It’s quite humid and the only place you get is the outside to sit if you come along with your pet.

I missed taking pictures of the food, but would surely do that the next time I make a visit.

From the pages you would think that it is a 4 star hotel but in actuality it lacks a lot.

1. On checkin the check-in desk was swamped and I was bluntly told to pay the full remaining balance. When I pointed out that I had not even checked in I was told it was hotel policy. The check-in personnel even forgot to ask me for my ID card which I had to remind him.

2. After coming to the room I discovered that the flush was not working. So again called up reception and they promised to fix it up. Which to their credit they did.

3. After having lunch I was told to pay direct to the restaurant. When I requested that they tab it to my room they said that they cannot do it for me. Same for dinner.

4. Next morning as I started to prepare the morning tea I found that the water heater was not working. Again called the reception and it took half hour to sort the stuff.

5. The bathroom drainage was faulty and water spolled around the bath tub. Not much but sufficient to irritate you.

5. The hotel advertises a 24 hour check in check out policy. No where is it mentioned that they count every 24 hours from your check-in as one day stay. Although they say they tell it during checkin but I was never told.  I had planned to check out at 02:30 pm as my flight was at 05:30 pm; but I was called up at 01:30 pm and asked to vacate the room else they would charge me for one more day. So I had to leave and kill time at the airport.

Small issues like these let this hotel down. Food is on the costly side. Service needs a major uphaul. They survive majorly on corporate bookings and as such individual books are low priority. Not staying here again

Disappointing Stay at Quality Inn Chennai

I recently stayed at Quality Inn Chennai, and unfortunately, my experience was less than satisfactory. Upon check-in, I was given two single beds instead of the king-size bed I had requested. Despite continuous follow-up, the issue was only resolved the next day.

Attempting to change the hotel but it was late at night was not feasible, given my short two-day stay. The overall stay was marred by a sense of congestion, making it feel suffocating. This experience fell short of the expected quality, and I hope the hotel addresses these issues for future guests.

I recently stayed at this hotel and unfortunately, the experience fell short of my expectations. The room's quality was poor, with dated and dull infrastructure and subpar linen. The toilets are not well-maintained, and I encountered a cleanliness issue with a dead fly in the basin upon check-in, which remained unaddressed. Improvement is needed for this establishment to truly live up to its 4-star rating.

While the staff demonstrated helpfulness with room service and a welcoming attitude at the reception, these positive aspects contrasted with the overall experience. Despite the friendly service, the room quality, linen, and maintenance concerns still need attention for a more satisfying stay.
